{"id":456,"date":"2021-02-07T12:04:46","date_gmt":"2021-02-07T12:04:46","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/dev.demowebcloud.com\/?page_id=456"},"modified":"2021-03-26T12:37:14","modified_gmt":"2021-03-26T12:37:14","slug":"thematic-working-areas","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-working-areas\/","title":{"rendered":"Thematic Areas"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><section class=\"kc-elm kc-css-465881 kc_row\"><div class=\"kc-row-container  kc-container\"><div class=\"kc-wrap-columns\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-855676 kc_col-sm-12 kc_column kc_col-sm-12\"><div class=\"kc-col-container\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-641571 kc_accordion_wrapper\">\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-963588 kc_accordion_section group \"><h3 class=\"kc_accordion_header ui-accordion-header\"><span class=\"ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon\"><\/span><a href=\"#climate-change\" data-prevent=\"scroll\"><i class=\"\"><\/i> Climate change<\/a><\/h3><div class=\"kc_accordion_content ui-accordion-content kc_clearfix\"><div class=\"kc-panel-body\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-639406 kc_text_block\"><\/p>\n<p>NACOM integrates climate change issue in their resource management programs because climate change and climate variability have potential adverse impacts on local biodiversity, fisheries, agriculture and livelihood of people. Therefore, planning and implementation of any biodiversity management and livelihood improvement schemes must consider and integrate the climate change elements. Considering this NACOM has implemented a number of climate change related research and adaptation projects in Bangladesh.<\/p>\n<p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-625040 kc_accordion_section group \"><h3 class=\"kc_accordion_header ui-accordion-header\"><span class=\"ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon\"><\/span><a href=\"#biodiversity-conservation\" data-prevent=\"scroll\"><i class=\"\"><\/i> Biodiversity conservation<\/a><\/h3><div class=\"kc_accordion_content ui-accordion-content kc_clearfix\"><div class=\"kc-panel-body\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-213969 kc_text_block\"><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">Bangladesh is a highly resourceful but over-populated country where the environment and rich tropical biodiversity has been degraded due to population pressure, lack of proper management and over exploitation of resources have been declining, ecosystems degrading and a lot of species are under threat of extinction. For halting this devastation and improving the biodiversity NACOM is working countrywide in multiple projects for biodiversity conservation.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-961188 kc_accordion_section group \"><h3 class=\"kc_accordion_header ui-accordion-header\"><span class=\"ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon\"><\/span><a href=\"#forest-management\" data-prevent=\"scroll\"><i class=\"\"><\/i> Forest management<\/a><\/h3><div class=\"kc_accordion_content ui-accordion-content kc_clearfix\"><div class=\"kc-panel-body\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-651037 kc_text_block\"><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">Bangladesh has a diminutive but species rich tropical forest areas. Over extraction and lack of resource management has led to near threatening state of our forest resources. NACOM works in forest conservation by providing alternative livelihoods for locals, forest-mangrove regeneration and re-plantation and conservation.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-202204 kc_accordion_section group \"><h3 class=\"kc_accordion_header ui-accordion-header\"><span class=\"ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon\"><\/span><a href=\"#species-conservation\" data-prevent=\"scroll\"><i class=\"\"><\/i> Species conservation<\/a><\/h3><div class=\"kc_accordion_content ui-accordion-content kc_clearfix\"><div class=\"kc-panel-body\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-319338 kc_text_block\"><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">pecies specific conservation of animal and plants are often required to protect and rejuvenate the declining species. We have extensive experiences and skills in conserving and rehabilitating the endangered species. And in our various NRM projects, we have species specific protection activities. We have successful records in conserving marine turtle, Pallas\u2019s Fishing Eagle and Spoon-billed sand piper and other threatened species.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-539117 kc_accordion_section group \"><h3 class=\"kc_accordion_header ui-accordion-header\"><span class=\"ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon\"><\/span><a href=\"#wetlands-resource-management\" data-prevent=\"scroll\"><i class=\"\"><\/i> Wetlands resource management<\/a><\/h3><div class=\"kc_accordion_content ui-accordion-content kc_clearfix\"><div class=\"kc-panel-body\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-752758 kc_text_block\"><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">Bangladesh has extensive biodiversity rich wetlands which are being depleted and over exploited due to human pressure. For addressing the issues NACOM has implemented various themes and is working around the clock to ensure the improvement, restoration of wetlands. We are working in selected areas of the Padma-Jamuna and Bharmaputra flood plain and coastal areas specially coxes bazar.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-233417 kc_accordion_section group \"><h3 class=\"kc_accordion_header ui-accordion-header\"><span class=\"ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon\"><\/span><a href=\"#energy-conservation\" data-prevent=\"scroll\"><i class=\"\"><\/i> Energy conservation<\/a><\/h3><div class=\"kc_accordion_content ui-accordion-content kc_clearfix\"><div class=\"kc-panel-body\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-168968 kc_text_block\"><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">As a strategy for reducing pressure on plant resources and fossil fuel, and facilitating climate change adaptation, NACOM promotes ICS, solar panel and biogas plants among rural communities. We have extensive experiences in promoting those alternate energy source and fuel saving innovations.\u00a0 Promotion of these innovations is an integral part of our most Natural Resource Management (NRM) Projects.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-310627 kc_accordion_section group \"><h3 class=\"kc_accordion_header ui-accordion-header\"><span class=\"ui-accordion-header-icon ui-icon\"><\/span><a href=\"#livelihood-development\" data-prevent=\"scroll\"><i class=\"\"><\/i> Livelihood Development<\/a><\/h3><div class=\"kc_accordion_content ui-accordion-content kc_clearfix\"><div class=\"kc-panel-body\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-800148 kc_text_block\"><\/p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">Poverty has been identified as one of the major causes for resource degradation. NACOM and its partners recognize the issue and believe that resources are better managed when the socio-economic conditions of the local people are better. NACOM gives emphasis on the poverty alleviation and undertakes programs on providing alternate source for income generation of the local poor people. Such alternate activities are eco-friendly. Our strategic approaches for livelihood development include the following:<\/p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">Providing household level production technology for IGA<\/p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">Livelihood skill development<\/p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; color: #555555; font-family: Cambria, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; word-spacing: 1px;\">Revolving fund and saving scheme management<\/p>\n<p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/section><section class=\"kc-elm kc-css-173825 kc_row\"><div class=\"kc-row-container  kc-container\"><div class=\"kc-wrap-columns\"><div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-615550 kc_col-sm-12 kc_column kc_col-sm-12\"><div class=\"kc-col-container\">\n<div class=\"kc-elm kc-css-706956 kc-blog-posts kc-blog-posts-2 kc-image-align-both\">\n\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"kc-list-item-2\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post_details\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"post-title-alt\"><a\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\thref=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/biodiversity-conservation-and-nature-based-solution\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttitle=\"Biodiversity Conservation and Nature Based Solution\">Biodiversity Conservation and Nature Based Solution<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Sixth mass extinction of global biodiversity is underway. Increased anthropogenic pressures on natural resources have been threatening existence of thousands of species including human being. NACOM comes up with nature-based sustainable solution in protecting biological diversity for better mankind. Since last four decades, NACOM has been significantly contributing in conservation&hellip;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/biodiversity-conservation-and-nature-based-solution\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t   class=\"kc-post-2-button\">Details <i\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"fa fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-right\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/7.-Common20Sandpiper1-543x304xct.jpg\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t     alt=\"Biodiversity Conservation and Nature Based Solution\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"kc-list-item-2\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/1.-Regenerated-Mangreove-forest-at-Nuniarchara-in-Coxs-Bazar-543x304xct.jpg\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t     alt=\"Natural Resource Management (NRM)\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-right\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post_details\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"post-title-alt\"><a\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\thref=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/natural-resource-management-nrm\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttitle=\"Natural Resource Management (NRM)\">Natural Resource Management (NRM)<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Sustainable utilization of major natural resources, such as land, water, air, minerals, forests, fisheries, and wild flora and fauna refers to the Natural Resource Management. NACOM\u2019s most mandates relate to conservation and management of renewable natural resources and have credible success stories in this area of work. NACOM has a&hellip;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/natural-resource-management-nrm\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t   class=\"kc-post-2-button\">Details <i\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"fa fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"kc-list-item-2\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post_details\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"post-title-alt\"><a\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\thref=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/forest-resource-management\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttitle=\"Forest Resource Management\">Forest Resource Management<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Forest is an important shelter and protector of biodiversity and Ecology. Also, forest plays important role of a carbon sink for mitigating the impact of Climate Change. As Bangladesh is one of the most vulnerable countries, protection of forest can help Bangladesh in many ways, especially by protecting coastal population&hellip;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/forest-resource-management\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t   class=\"kc-post-2-button\">Details <i\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"fa fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-right\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Sairakhali-Fasiakhali-beat-2017-Assisted-Naturally-Regenrated-Forest-Area-543x304xct.jpg\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t     alt=\"Forest Resource Management\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"kc-list-item-2\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/2.-Climate-Smart-Agriculture-543x304xct.jpeg\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t     alt=\"Climate Change and Resilience\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-right\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post_details\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"post-title-alt\"><a\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\thref=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/climate-change-and-resilience\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttitle=\"Climate Change and Resilience\">Climate Change and Resilience<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>NACOM integrates climate change issue in their resource management programs because climate change and climate variability have potential adverse impacts on local biodiversity, fisheries, agriculture and livelihood of people. For the people of Bangladesh, climate change is not just something they read about in newspapers \u2013 it is a reality&hellip;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/climate-change-and-resilience\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t   class=\"kc-post-2-button\">Details <i\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"fa fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"kc-list-item-2\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post_details\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"post-title-alt\"><a\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\thref=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/clean-energy-and-energy-conservation\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttitle=\"Clean Energy and Energy Conservation\">Clean Energy and Energy Conservation<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/h2>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>One of the major factors of the climate change is the generation and consumption of the energy. Apart from climate change issue, different energy poses serious threat to the human health and create pressure on natural resources as well. As a strategy for reducing pressure on forest\/natural resources and fossil&hellip;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/clean-energy-and-energy-conservation\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t   class=\"kc-post-2-button\">Details <i\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tclass=\"fa fa-angle-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><\/i><\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-right\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/1.-Promotion-of-the-Biomass-Briquettes-scaled-543x304xct.jpg\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t     alt=\"Clean Energy and Energy Conservation\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"kc-list-item-2\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/2.-Livelihood-support-for-the-Covid-19affected-group-USAIDs-ECO-LIFE-Activity-scaled-543x304xct.jpg\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t     alt=\"Livelihood Support Services\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post-item-right\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post_details\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"post-title-alt\"><a\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\thref=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/livelihood-support-services\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\ttitle=\"Livelihood Support Services\">Livelihood Support Services<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/h2>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Poverty has been identified as one of the major causes for natural resource degradation. NACOM recognizes the issue and believes that resources are better managed when the socio-economic conditions of the local people are better. NACOM gives emphasis on the poverty alleviation and undertakes programs on providing alternate source for&hellip;<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https:\/\/nacom.org\/thematic-areas\/livelihood-support-services\/\"\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t   class=\"kc-post-2-button\">Details <i\n\t\